column4: High mountains coated with snow blocks. This was made to resemble the mountain range located in Central Europe.
A flat marsh biome of willow trees with green murky water.
The Bog consists of small Oak and Spruce scrubs, as well as Sweet Berry Bushes. Based on a Cranberry Bog.
A beautiful and wondrous biome containing lush-coloured grass with Pink and White Cherry Trees.
Gigantic fir tree forests with a cool temperature and dull colored grass.
Nether biome with crystals
Dying forest full of sparsely populated trees.
Jungles with Giant Glowshrooms and Oak bushes across the ground.
Beautiful Spruce Pear-Shaped trees make up this biome of green grass.
This biome consists of rough, high terrain with cobblestone boulders and lacks trees.
Twisting jade-coloured mountain cliffs covered with spruce trees, and spruce bushes.
Beautiful fields of lavender and jacaranda trees, with the occasional oak tree
Desert made of orange sand and flourishing, but messy trees. Unlike deserts, lush deserts have more vegetation.
A grassy biome with a few spruce trees and bushes scattered around.
Majestic grove of purple waters and beautiful enchanted trees. It is rare to find, though.
Dark Purple woods with a special sky and water colour. Several dangerous plants can spawn here. Beware
Formerly a sub-biome for the plains, it is now fields of large oak trees and bright grass.
A biome with light-colored grass and several trees scattered.
A lush biome with many flowering oak trees.
A forest of tall Redwood Trees and lots of ferns. This was made to resemble the Redwood Forests in Northern California.
Forests of tall birch and oak trees with different colored autumn leaves.
Dry Grassland with mixed Acacia and Spruce scrubs
A relatively flat biome with oak shrubs and many allium flowers.
A rare swampy biome with many patches of cobwebs on ground and trees. The foliage shows its dark, dull color
Snowy variant of the Coniferous Forest biome.
A snowless wasteland of shrubs and cobblestone.
A hazy biome with pools of murky brown water. Dead trees also appear in this biome. It is an inhospitable place, and not recommended for beginners.
Lush swamps with a deep blue water color and willow trees
A beach made entirely of gravel, mainly spawns adjacent to Woodland or other temperate biomes
Where it all started: A perfect replica of the original Minecraft Classic, including roses which were removed in vanilla 1.7.
A beautiful, but extremely rare island biome with Rainbow Birch Trees all over the place.
A rare island biome with palm trees and bright blue skies. Sub-biome of the Ocean.

A desolate biome with lots of lava. This biome used to generate in large areas, but can only be found as a rare ocean sub-biome island in later versions. It is dangerous, note the lava and steep incline.
A nether biome that contains bone columns and flesh tendons.
A vast expanse of flat terrain with tulips on almost every piece of ground. Replaced with Flower Meadow in 1.13.2.
Grass and sand
Nether Biome, some trees
Nether biome.  Blackstone and obsidian ground
Dried salt ground, sparse dried trees.  Brownish water
Similar to a taiga with fewer trees
Some shorter redwood trees
White sand, blue waters
Nether biome? Ash ground, small shrubs, one-high trees
